      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That \"pop\" likely indicates a sudden change in ear pressure, possibly an Eustachian tube dysfunction or a minor barotrauma, which often causes temporary hearing loss and tinnitus. While it could resolve on its own, total unilateral hearing loss requires professional evaluation to rule out more serious conditions like sudden sensorineural hearing loss. Given the severity of the total hearing loss and the potential for time-sensitive treatment, I strongly advise seeking medical help from an ENT specialist at an urgent clinic or hospital immediately rather than waiting, especially since you are in Oslo.",
