      "content": "While earwax is a possibility, \"total\" hearing loss after a loud pop is a medical emergency until proven otherwise, as it could indicate sudden sensorineural hearing loss requiring treatment within 24-48 hours. Wax impaction rarely causes sudden, complete silence immediately after hearing a pop, which points more likely to issues in the inner ear or nerve.\n\nDelaying care until tomorrow morning risks permanent hearing damage, even if the cause is unusually simple. Please consult a local urgent care clinic or open hospital ward in Oslo now for a professional diagnosis and potential fitting of earplugs if it is simply wet or blocked. Ignoring sudden, total hearing loss is dangerous regardless of whether drops might help.",
